<!-- doc/src/sgml/passwordcheck.sgml -->

<sect1 id="passwordcheck" xreflabel="passwordcheck">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=6dd358cd6a1511aeaac20a335ed1e290 sig_cn_org=248980883fcb54f9b12ee63166ea3f1a source=16.8 
 <title>passwordcheck &mdash; verify password strength</title>
________________________________________________________-->
 <title>passwordcheck &mdash; 验证密码强度</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=6dd358cd6a1511aeaac20a335ed1e290 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f14342987c431813a9a57b9bdbb6eecf sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
 <indexterm zone="passwordcheck">
  <primary>passwordcheck</primary>
 </indexterm>
________________________________________________________-->
 <indexterm zone="passwordcheck">
  <primary>passwordcheck</primary>
 </indexterm>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f14342987c431813a9a57b9bdbb6eecf -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=860bd1d57af65aaecc1e967f0b357804 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
 <para>
  The <filename>passwordcheck</filename> module checks users' passwords
  whenever they are set with
  <xref linkend="sql-createrole"/> or
  <xref linkend="sql-alterrole"/>.
  If a password is considered too weak, it will be rejected and
  the command will terminate with an error.
 </para>
________________________________________________________-->
 <para>
  只要通过<xref linkend="sql-createrole"/>或<xref linkend="sql-alterrole"/>设置用户，
  <filename>passwordcheck</filename>模块会检查用户的密码。如果一个密码被认为太弱，它将被拒绝并且该命令将带着一个错误终止。
 </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=860bd1d57af65aaecc1e967f0b357804 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=aa707b1ee43f417f7c4862f6ab737532 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
 <para>
  To enable this module, add <literal>'$libdir/passwordcheck'</literal>
  to <xref linkend="guc-shared-preload-libraries"/> in
  <filename>postgresql.conf</filename>, then restart the server.
 </para>
________________________________________________________-->
 <para>
  要启用这个模块，把<literal>'$libdir/passwordcheck'</literal>加入到<filename>postgresql.conf</filename>中的<xref linkend="guc-shared-preload-libraries"/>，然后重启服务器。
 </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=aa707b1ee43f417f7c4862f6ab737532 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=71b123264a95707a7bc9ab8f5ce378e4 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
 <para>
  You can adapt this module to your needs by changing the source code.
  For example, you can use
  <ulink url="https://github.com/cracklib/cracklib">CrackLib</ulink>
  to check passwords &mdash; this only requires uncommenting
  two lines in the <filename>Makefile</filename> and rebuilding the
  module.  (We cannot include <productname>CrackLib</productname>
  by default for license reasons.)
  Without <productname>CrackLib</productname>, the module enforces a few
  simple rules for password strength, which you can modify or extend
  as you see fit.
 </para>
________________________________________________________-->
 <para>
  你可以通过修改源代码来按你的需要修改这个模块。例如，你可以使用<ulink url="https://github.com/cracklib/cracklib">CrackLib</ulink>来检查密码 &mdash; 这只需要在<filename>Makefile</filename>中取消两行的注释并且重新编译该模块（由于授权原因，我们不能默认包括<productname>CrackLib</productname>）。如果没有<productname>CrackLib</productname>，该模块会对密码强度强制一些简单的规则，你可以自行修改和扩充。
 </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=71b123264a95707a7bc9ab8f5ce378e4 -->

 <caution>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=33538c80ed8a375e9c7db5c34e21fde9 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
  <para>
   To prevent unencrypted passwords from being sent across the network,
   written to the server log or otherwise stolen by a database administrator,
   <productname>PostgreSQL</productname> allows the user to supply
   pre-encrypted passwords. Many client programs make use of this
   functionality and encrypt the password before sending it to the server.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   要阻止未加密的密码被通过网络传送、写入到服务器日志或者被一个数据库管理员窃取，<productname>PostgreSQL</productname>允许用户提供预加密的密码。很多客户端程序利用这种功能并且在把密码发送给服务器之前加密它。
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=33538c80ed8a375e9c7db5c34e21fde9 -->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5324c1d87965eb89ef999e9047141b51 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
  <para>
   This limits the usefulness of the <filename>passwordcheck</filename>
   module, because in that case it can only try to guess the password.
   For this reason, <filename>passwordcheck</filename> is not
   recommended if your security requirements are high.
   It is more secure to use an external authentication method such as GSSAPI
   (see <xref linkend="client-authentication"/>) than to rely on
   passwords within the database.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   这限制了<filename>passwordcheck</filename>模块的有用性，因为这种情况下它只能尝试猜测密码。由于这个原因，如果你的安全性需求很高，我们不推荐<filename>passwordcheck</filename>。使用一个诸如 GSSAPI （见<xref linkend="client-authentication"/>）的外部认证方法比依赖数据库内的密码更加安全。
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5324c1d87965eb89ef999e9047141b51 -->
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=829478c9860541f9c1e0cd814c42defb sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
  <para>
   Alternatively, you could modify <filename>passwordcheck</filename>
   to reject pre-encrypted passwords, but forcing users to set their
   passwords in clear text carries its own security risks.
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   此外，你可以修改<filename>passwordcheck</filename>来拒绝预加密的密码，但是强制用户将密码设置为明文带来了它的安全风险。
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=829478c9860541f9c1e0cd814c42defb -->
 </caution>

 <sect2 id="passwordcheck-configuration-parameters">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9125daac1844cde69a678e3c3c9c9bcf sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
  <title>Configuration Parameters</title>
________________________________________________________-->
  <title>配置参数</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9125daac1844cde69a678e3c3c9c9bcf -->

  <variablelist>
   <varlistentry>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=50fca0c25bfd0c501d19e1528bf12039 sig_cn_org=08835e64ccf04afff8c70b646fa722e1 source=18.3 
    <term>
     <varname>passwordcheck.min_password_length</varname> (<type>integer</type>)
     <indexterm>
      <primary><varname>passwordcheck.min_password_length</varname> configuration parameter</primary>
     </indexterm>
    </term>
________________________________________________________-->
    <term>
     <varname>passwordcheck.min_password_length</varname> (<type>integer</type>)
     <indexterm>
      <primary><varname>passwordcheck.min_password_length</varname> 配置参数</primary>
     </indexterm>
    </term>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=50fca0c25bfd0c501d19e1528bf12039 -->
    <listitem>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=85eacba2ec5813677091cbb3938357bc sig_cn_org=80401ccbe0f2f9b3720aa7199407175d source=18.3 
     <para>
      The minimum acceptable password length in bytes.  The default is 8.  Only
      superusers can change this setting.
     </para>
________________________________________________________-->
     <para>
      可接受的最小密码长度（以字节为单位）。默认值为 8。只有
      超级用户可以更改此设置。
     </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=85eacba2ec5813677091cbb3938357bc -->
     <note>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=0f933b37d426967c9f7b2192d775cfaf sig_cn_org=5a3eb958539e7a45fd33cbb22cb4ee69 source=18.3 
      <para>
       This parameter has no effect if a user supplies a pre-encrypted
       password.
      </para>
________________________________________________________-->
      <para>
       如果用户提供了预加密的密码，则此参数无效。
      </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=0f933b37d426967c9f7b2192d775cfaf -->
     </note>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=f5baf48bcf1d94f26906905c95fa47c3 sig_cn_org=fde9005e4ed3e6e056ec85cf2f84edc8 source=18.3 
  <para>
   In ordinary usage, this parameter is set in
   <filename>postgresql.conf</filename>, but superusers can alter it on-the-fly
   within their own sessions.  Typical usage might be:
  </para>
________________________________________________________-->
  <para>
   在普通使用中，此参数在
   <filename>postgresql.conf</filename> 中设置，但超级用户可以在自己的会话中动态更改它。典型用法可能是：
  </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=f5baf48bcf1d94f26906905c95fa47c3 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=983de0b7add7783be15169d37dbb413d sig_cn_org=2a623e44d0b390b2d908074d14a914e1 source=18.3 
<programlisting>
# postgresql.conf
passwordcheck.min_password_length = 12
</programlisting>
________________________________________________________-->
<programlisting>
# postgresql.conf
passwordcheck.min_password_length = 12
</programlisting>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=983de0b7add7783be15169d37dbb413d -->
 </sect2>
</sect1>
